At Palumba, we are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data in an open and transparent manner. We process personal information in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other applicable privacy laws.
Data Processor
We use Fathom Analytics, a privacy-focused analytics service that complies with GDPR, ePrivacy Directive (including PECR), COPPA, and CCPA. Fathom Analytics does not use cookies and only briefly processes IP addresses to gather statistical data without identifying individual users. You can find more information about Fathom Analytics and its privacy practices on their website.
Purpose of Data Processing
The primary purpose for using Fathom Analytics is to analyse website traffic in order to continuously improve our website and service offerings. This processing of data is based on our legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR), specifically to enhance user experience and optimize our business operations.
Data De-Identification
In line with CCPA requirements, all personal information processed by us is de-identified to ensure that no individual can be identified through the data we collect.
Data Controller
The data controller for this website is Associació Juvenil Palumba EU, located in Barcelona, Spain, with ID number ES-G70743836.
Your Rights Under GDPR
Under the GDPR, you have various rights regarding your personal data, including:
The right to access the personal data we hold about you.
The right to request the correction of inaccurate data.
The right to request deletion of your personal data when it’s no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected.
The right to object to the processing of your personal data.
The right to request the restriction of processing concerning your data.
The right to data portability, allowing you to obtain and reuse your personal data for your own purposes across different services.
Data Retention
We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy statement, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
Contact Information
For any questions or concerns regarding your privacy, you can contact us.
Changes to This Privacy Statement
We reserve the right to modify this privacy statement at any time, so please review it frequently. Changes and clarifications will take effect immediately upon their posting on the website.
Effective Date
This privacy statement was last updated on 18/04/2024.